Brocal and Sebastián (2015b) analyzed the NERs included in the four specific reports on emerging physical risks (Flaspöler et al., 2005), emerging biological risks (Brun et al., 2007a), emerging psychosocial risks (Brun et al., 2007b), and emerging chemical risks (Brun et al., 2009). These authors considered only the NERs classified as “risk strongly agreed as emerging” and “risk agreed as emerging.” Each risk classified as “undecided,” “there is agreement that the risk is not emerging,” and “there is strong agreement that the risk is not emerging,” cannot be considered as NER. Among the results obtained, Brocal and Sebastián (2015b) identified a set of technological aspects (Table 2.10
) and organizational aspects (Table 2.11
) linked to advanced manufacturing processes.
